User & Disk Management Feature

 Context

 The NAS dashboard needs admin panels for managing system users and disks. These are root-only operations — only visible and functional when the
 active session belongs to root (uid=0, gid=0).

 Architecture Decision

 Use DEFINE_AUTH_ROUTE for all admin endpoints. Since fork_and_run() drops to the authenticated user's uid, a root session's handler runs as root
 and can execute privileged operations. Each handler guards with if (getuid() != 0) → 403. This keeps privilege separation intact — non-root users
  simply get rejected.

